var documenterSearchIndex = {"docs":
[{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#graph_memory","page":"Graph Memory","text":"Graph memory adds structured knowledge representation to Mem0.jl's vector-based memory system. While vector search finds semantically similar memories, graph memory captures explicit entity-relationship triples (e.g., \"Alice → works_at → Acme Corp\") for precise, structured retrieval.","title":"Graph Memory"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Why-Graph-Memory?","page":"Graph Memory","text":"Vector search excels at finding \"related\" memories, but it can struggle with:\n\nPrecise relationships: \"Who does Alice work for?\" requires understanding a specific relationship, not just semantic similarity.\nMulti-hop reasoning: \"What company does the person who likes Julia work for?\" requires traversing relationships.\nStructured queries: Finding all entities of a certain type or all relationships of a certain kind.\n\nGraph memory complements vector search by maintaining a knowledge graph of entities and their relationships, extracted automatically by the LLM.","title":"Why Graph Memory?"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#How-It-Works","page":"Graph Memory","text":"When graph memory is enabled, every call to add performs two parallel operations:\n\nVector pipeline — extracts facts, embeds them, stores in vector store (as usual)\nGraph pipeline — extracts entities and relationships, stores them as nodes and edges\n\n\"Alice works at Acme Corp and loves Julia\"\n    │\n    ├─ Vector: \"Works at Acme Corp\" (embedded and stored)\n    │          \"Loves Julia programming language\" (embedded and stored)\n    │\n    └─ Graph:  alice ──works_at──► acme_corp\n               alice ──loves────► julia\n\nSimilarly, search queries both the vector store and graph store, returning results in \"results\" and \"relations\" keys respectively.","title":"How It Works"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Entity-and-Relationship-Extraction","page":"Graph Memory","text":"The graph store uses LLM-based extraction with tool calling:\n\nEntity extraction — identifies named entities and their types (person, organization, technology, etc.)\nRelationship extraction — identifies directed relationships between entities (worksat, likes, livesin, etc.)\n\nEntity names are normalized to lowercase with underscores (e.g., \"Acme Corp\" → acme_corp). Similar entities are deduplicated using embedding cosine similarity above the configured threshold.","title":"Entity and Relationship Extraction"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#InMemoryGraphStore-Setup","page":"Graph Memory","text":"The simplest way to enable graph memory:\n\nusing Mem0\n\nconfig = MemoryConfig(\n    llm = LlmConfig(\n        provider = \"ollama\",\n        config = Dict(\"model\" => \"qwen2.5\"),\n    ),\n    embedder = EmbedderConfig(\n        provider = \"ollama\",\n        config = Dict(\"model\" => \"nomic-embed-text\", \"embedding_dims\" => 768),\n    ),\n    vector_store = VectorStoreConfig(\n        provider = \"in_memory\",\n        config = Dict(\"collection_name\" => \"test\", \"embedding_model_dims\" => 768),\n    ),\n    graph_store = GraphStoreConfig(\n        provider = \"in_memory\",\n        config = Dict{String, Any}(),  # non-nothing value enables graph memory\n        threshold = 0.7,               # entity matching similarity threshold\n    ),\n)\n\nmem = Memory(config=config)\n\nnote: Enabling graph memory\nGraph memory is disabled when graph_store.config is nothing (the default). Set it to any Dict — even an empty one — to enable it.","title":"InMemoryGraphStore Setup"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Neo4jGraphStore-Setup","page":"Graph Memory","text":"For production use, Neo4jGraphStore persists the knowledge graph in Neo4j:","title":"Neo4jGraphStore Setup"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Prerequisites","page":"Graph Memory","text":"Install and run Neo4j\nEnsure the HTTP API is accessible (default: port 7474)","title":"Prerequisites"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Configuration","page":"Graph Memory","text":"config = MemoryConfig(\n    llm = LlmConfig(provider=\"ollama\", config=Dict(\"model\" => \"qwen2.5\")),\n    embedder = EmbedderConfig(provider=\"ollama\", config=Dict(\"model\" => \"nomic-embed-text\", \"embedding_dims\" => 768)),\n    vector_store = VectorStoreConfig(provider=\"in_memory\", config=Dict(\"collection_name\" => \"test\", \"embedding_model_dims\" => 768)),\n    graph_store = GraphStoreConfig(\n        provider = \"neo4j\",\n        config = Dict{String, Any}(\n            \"url\" => \"http://localhost:7474\",\n            \"username\" => \"neo4j\",\n            \"password\" => \"your-password\",\n            \"database\" => \"neo4j\",\n        ),\n        threshold = 0.7,\n    ),\n)\n\nmem = Memory(config=config)","title":"Configuration"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#URL-Formats","page":"Graph Memory","text":"The url config key accepts multiple formats:\n\nhttp://localhost:7474 — direct HTTP API URL\nhttps://my-neo4j.example.com:7473 — HTTPS\nbolt://localhost:7687 — host is extracted, HTTP port 7474 is used\nneo4j://localhost:7687 — same as bolt","title":"URL Formats"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Authentication","page":"Graph Memory","text":"Neo4j requires username and password in the config. These are sent as HTTP Basic Auth to the Transactional Cypher API.","title":"Authentication"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Using-a-Separate-LLM-for-Graph-Extraction","page":"Graph Memory","text":"You can use a different (potentially more capable) LLM for graph entity/relationship extraction:\n\ngraph_store = GraphStoreConfig(\n    provider = \"neo4j\",\n    config = Dict{String, Any}(\n        \"url\" => \"http://localhost:7474\",\n        \"username\" => \"neo4j\",\n        \"password\" => \"password\",\n    ),\n    llm = LlmConfig(\n        provider = \"openai\",\n        config = Dict(\"model\" => \"gpt-4.1-mini-2025-04-14\"),\n    ),\n    threshold = 0.7,\n)\n\nIf graph_store.llm is nothing, the main MemoryConfig.llm is used instead.","title":"Using a Separate LLM for Graph Extraction"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Combined-Vector-Graph-Search","page":"Graph Memory","text":"When graph memory is enabled, search automatically queries both stores:\n\nresults = search(mem, \"What does Alice do?\"; user_id=\"alice\")\n\n# Vector results (semantic similarity)\nfor r in results[\"results\"]\n    println(\"Memory: \", r[\"memory\"], \" (score: \", r[\"score\"], \")\")\nend\n\n# Graph results (entity relationships)\nfor rel in get(results, \"relations\", [])\n    println(rel[\"source\"], \" --\", rel[\"relationship\"], \"--> \", rel[\"destination\"])\nend\n\nSimilarly, get_all returns both \"results\" (vector) and \"relations\" (graph) when graph memory is enabled.","title":"Combined Vector + Graph Search"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Graph-Specific-Operations","page":"Graph Memory","text":"You can also interact with the graph store directly through these functions:","title":"Graph-Specific Operations"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Adding-to-the-Graph","page":"Graph Memory","text":"add_to_graph! extracts entities and relationships from text and stores them:\n\nadd_to_graph!(mem.graph, \"Alice works at Acme Corp\", Dict(\"user_id\" => \"alice\"))","title":"Adding to the Graph"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Searching-the-Graph","page":"Graph Memory","text":"search_graph finds entities similar to the query and returns connected relationships:\n\nrelations = search_graph(mem.graph, \"Alice\", Dict(\"user_id\" => \"alice\"); limit=10)\nfor rel in relations\n    println(rel[\"source\"], \" → \", rel[\"relationship\"], \" → \", rel[\"destination\"])\nend","title":"Searching the Graph"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Retrieving-All-Relationships","page":"Graph Memory","text":"get_all_graph returns all valid relationships matching the filters:\n\nall_rels = get_all_graph(mem.graph, Dict(\"user_id\" => \"alice\"); limit=100)","title":"Retrieving All Relationships"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Deleting-from-the-Graph","page":"Graph Memory","text":"delete_from_graph! soft-deletes relationships matching the data and filters:\n\ndelete_from_graph!(mem.graph, \"Alice works at Acme Corp\", Dict(\"user_id\" => \"alice\"))\n\ndelete_all_graph! soft-deletes (in-memory) or hard-deletes (Neo4j) all matching relationships:\n\ndelete_all_graph!(mem.graph, Dict(\"user_id\" => \"alice\"))","title":"Deleting from the Graph"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Custom-Extraction-Prompts","page":"Graph Memory","text":"You can customize how relationships are extracted by setting custom_prompt on the graph store config:\n\ngraph_store = GraphStoreConfig(\n    provider = \"in_memory\",\n    config = Dict{String, Any}(),\n    custom_prompt = \"\"\"\n    Focus on professional and organizational relationships.\n    Extract relationships like: works_at, manages, reports_to, collaborates_with.\n    Ignore personal preferences and casual mentions.\n    \"\"\",\n)","title":"Custom Extraction Prompts"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/graph_memory.html#Entity-Similarity-Threshold","page":"Graph Memory","text":"The threshold parameter (default 0.7) controls how aggressively entities are deduplicated. When a new entity is extracted:\n\nIts name is embedded\nExisting nodes matching the filters are compared by cosine similarity\nIf any existing node scores ≥ threshold, it is reused instead of creating a new node\n\nLower thresholds merge more aggressively (risk of false merges); higher thresholds create more separate nodes (risk of duplicates).","title":"Entity Similarity Threshold"},{"category":"section","location":"api/types.html#types_api","page":"Types","text":"Core data types, configuration structs, enums, and exception types used throughout Mem0.jl.","title":"Types"},{"category":"section","location":"api/types.html#Configuration-Types","page":"Types","text":"","title":"Configuration Types"},{"category":"section","location":"api/types.html#Data-Types","page":"Types","text":"","title":"Data Types"},{"category":"section","location":"api/types.html#Memory-Type-Enum","page":"Types","text":"","title":"Memory Type Enum"},{"category":"section","location":"api/types.html#Internal-Data-Types","page":"Types","text":"","title":"Internal Data Types"},{"category":"section","location":"api/types.html#History-Manager","page":"Types","text":"","title":"History Manager"},{"category":"section","location":"api/types.html#Exceptions","page":"Types","text":"","title":"Exceptions"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.MemoryConfig","page":"Types","text":"MemoryConfig\n\nTop-level configuration for the Memory system.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.MemoryConfig"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.LlmConfig","page":"Types","text":"LLM provider configuration.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.LlmConfig"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.EmbedderConfig","page":"Types","text":"Embedding provider configuration.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.EmbedderConfig"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.VectorStoreConfig","page":"Types","text":"Vector store configuration.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.VectorStoreConfig"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.GraphStoreConfig","page":"Types","text":"Graph store configuration.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.GraphStoreConfig"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.RerankerConfig","page":"Types","text":"Reranker configuration.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.RerankerConfig"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.MemoryItem","page":"Types","text":"MemoryItem\n\nA single memory record returned from search/get operations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.MemoryItem"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.MemoryResult","page":"Types","text":"MemoryResult\n\nResult from add/search/get_all operations.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.MemoryResult"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.ChatMessage","page":"Types","text":"A chat message with role and content.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.ChatMessage"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.MemoryType","page":"Types","text":"Memory type classification.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.MemoryType"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.VectorRecord","page":"Types","text":"VectorRecord\n\nA single record in the vector store.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.VectorRecord"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.LLMResponse","page":"Types","text":"LLMResponse\n\nStandardized response from an LLM call.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.LLMResponse"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.HistoryManager","page":"Types","text":"HistoryManager\n\nThread-safe SQLite-based history tracker for memory operations (add, update, delete).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.HistoryManager"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.Mem0Error","page":"Types","text":"Mem0Error <: Exception\n\nBase exception for all Mem0 errors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.Mem0Error"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.Mem0ValidationError","page":"Types","text":"Mem0ValidationError <: Exception\n\nRaised when input validation fails (missing filters, invalid config, etc.).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.Mem0ValidationError"},{"category":"type","location":"api/types.html#Mem0.Mem0ProviderError","page":"Types","text":"Mem0ProviderError <: Exception\n\nRaised when an LLM, embedder, or vector store provider fails.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.Mem0ProviderError"},{"category":"section","location":"api/utilities.html#utilities_api","page":"Utilities","text":"Helper functions for message parsing, JSON extraction, hashing, filtering, vector math, history management, and graph operations.","title":"Utilities API"},{"category":"section","location":"api/utilities.html#Message-Parsing","page":"Utilities","text":"","title":"Message Parsing"},{"category":"section","location":"api/utilities.html#JSON-Utilities","page":"Utilities","text":"","title":"JSON Utilities"},{"category":"section","location":"api/utilities.html#Hashing-and-Normalization","page":"Utilities","text":"","title":"Hashing and Normalization"},{"category":"section","location":"api/utilities.html#Vector-Math","page":"Utilities","text":"","title":"Vector Math"},{"category":"section","location":"api/utilities.html#Filter-Construction","page":"Utilities","text":"","title":"Filter Construction"},{"category":"section","location":"api/utilities.html#History-Operations","page":"Utilities","text":"","title":"History Operations"},{"category":"section","location":"api/utilities.html#Graph-Operations","page":"Utilities","text":"","title":"Graph Operations"},{"category":"section","location":"api/utilities.html#Vector-Store-Operations","page":"Utilities","text":"","title":"Vector Store Operations"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.parse_messages","page":"Utilities","text":"parse_messages(messages)\n\nConvert a vector of message dicts to a formatted string with role prefixes.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.parse_messages"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.normalize_facts","page":"Utilities","text":"normalize_facts(raw_facts)\n\nNormalize LLM output of facts into a clean vector of strings. Handles strings, dicts with \"fact\"/\"text\" keys, and other formats.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.normalize_facts"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.extract_json","page":"Utilities","text":"extract_json(text)\n\nExtract JSON from text that may contain code blocks or other wrapping. Returns a parsed Dict/Vector or nothing if no valid JSON found.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.extract_json"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.remove_code_blocks","page":"Utilities","text":"remove_code_blocks(content)\n\nRemove markdown code blocks and <think> tags from content.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.remove_code_blocks"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.memory_hash","page":"Utilities","text":"memory_hash(text)\n\nGenerate an MD5 hash string for memory deduplication.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.memory_hash"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.normalize_entity","page":"Utilities","text":"normalize_entity(name)\n\nNormalize an entity name: lowercase, replace spaces with underscores.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.normalize_entity"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.now_iso","page":"Utilities","text":"now_iso()\n\nReturn the current time as an ISO 8601 string.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.now_iso"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.cosine_similarity","page":"Utilities","text":"cosine_similarity(a, b)\n\nCompute cosine similarity between two vectors.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.cosine_similarity"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.build_filters_and_metadata","page":"Utilities","text":"build_filters_and_metadata(; user_id=nothing, agent_id=nothing, run_id=nothing,\n                              input_metadata=nothing, input_filters=nothing)\n\nBuild metadata template and query filters from session IDs. Returns (metadata::Dict, filters::Dict).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.build_filters_and_metadata"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.add_history!","page":"Utilities","text":"add_history!(mgr, memory_id, old_memory, new_memory, event; kwargs...)\n\nInsert a history record for a memory operation.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.add_history!"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.get_history","page":"Utilities","text":"get_history(mgr, memory_id)\n\nRetrieve all history records for a given memory ID, ordered chronologically.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.get_history"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.reset_history!","page":"Utilities","text":"reset_history!(mgr)\n\nDrop and recreate the history table.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.reset_history!"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.add_to_graph!","page":"Utilities","text":"add_to_graph!(graph, data, filters)\n\nAdd entities and relationships extracted from data into the graph.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.add_to_graph!"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.search_graph","page":"Utilities","text":"search_graph(graph, query, filters; limit=100)\n\nSearch the graph for entities and relationships relevant to the query.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.search_graph"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.delete_from_graph!","page":"Utilities","text":"delete_from_graph!(graph, data, filters)\n\nSoft-delete relationships matching the data.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.delete_from_graph!"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.delete_all_graph!","page":"Utilities","text":"delete_all_graph!(graph, filters)\n\nDelete all entities/relationships matching the filters.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.delete_all_graph!"},{"category":"function","location":"api/utilities.html#Mem0.get_all_graph","page":"Utilities","text":"get_all_graph(graph, filters; limit=100)\n\nRetrieve all relationships matching filters.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.get_all_graph"},{"category":"section","location":"api/providers.html#providers_api","page":"Providers","text":"Abstract interfaces and concrete implementations for LLM, embedding, vector store, and graph store providers.","title":"Providers API"},{"category":"section","location":"api/providers.html#Abstract-Types","page":"Providers","text":"","title":"Abstract Types"},{"category":"section","location":"api/providers.html#LLM-Providers","page":"Providers","text":"","title":"LLM Providers"},{"category":"section","location":"api/providers.html#Embedding-Providers","page":"Providers","text":"","title":"Embedding Providers"},{"category":"section","location":"api/providers.html#Vector-Store-Providers","page":"Providers","text":"","title":"Vector Store Providers"},{"category":"section","location":"api/providers.html#Graph-Store-Providers","page":"Providers","text":"","title":"Graph Store Providers"},{"category":"section","location":"api/providers.html#Provider-Interface-Methods","page":"Providers","text":"","title":"Provider Interface Methods"},{"category":"section","location":"api/providers.html#Factory-Functions","page":"Providers","text":"","title":"Factory Functions"},{"category":"section","location":"api/providers.html#Provider-Registration","page":"Providers","text":"","title":"Provider Registration"},{"category":"type","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.AbstractLLM","page":"Providers","text":"AbstractLLM\n\nAbstract base type for language model providers.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.AbstractLLM"},{"category":"type","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.AbstractEmbedder","page":"Providers","text":"AbstractEmbedder\n\nAbstract base type for embedding model providers.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.AbstractEmbedder"},{"category":"type","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.AbstractVectorStore","page":"Providers","text":"AbstractVectorStore\n\nAbstract base type for vector store backends.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.AbstractVectorStore"},{"category":"type","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.AbstractGraphStore","page":"Providers","text":"AbstractGraphStore\n\nAbstract base type for graph memory backends. All concrete subtypes must have llm::AbstractLLM and custom_prompt::Union{Nothing, String} fields.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.AbstractGraphStore"},{"category":"type","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.OpenAILLM","page":"Providers","text":"OpenAILLM <: AbstractLLM\n\nOpenAI-compatible LLM provider using the Chat Completions API.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.OpenAILLM"},{"category":"type","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.OllamaLLM","page":"Providers","text":"OllamaLLM <: AbstractLLM\n\nOllama-compatible LLM provider using the local Ollama API.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.OllamaLLM"},{"category":"type","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.OpenAIEmbedding","page":"Providers","text":"OpenAIEmbedding <: AbstractEmbedder\n\nOpenAI embedding provider using the Embeddings API.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.OpenAIEmbedding"},{"category":"type","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.OllamaEmbedding","page":"Providers","text":"OllamaEmbedding <: AbstractEmbedder\n\nOllama embedding provider using the local Ollama API.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.OllamaEmbedding"},{"category":"type","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.InMemoryVectorStore","page":"Providers","text":"InMemoryVectorStore <: AbstractVectorStore\n\nA simple in-memory vector store using brute-force cosine similarity search. Suitable for development, testing, and small-scale deployments.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.InMemoryVectorStore"},{"category":"type","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.InMemoryGraphStore","page":"Providers","text":"InMemoryGraphStore <: AbstractGraphStore\n\nA simple in-memory graph store using adjacency lists. Supports entity embeddings for semantic search, soft-deletion, and multi-tenant filtering.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.InMemoryGraphStore"},{"category":"type","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.Neo4jGraphStore","page":"Providers","text":"Neo4jGraphStore <: AbstractGraphStore\n\nGraph store backed by Neo4j, accessed via the HTTP Transactional Cypher API. Stores entity embeddings as float-array node properties for client-side cosine similarity matching, and uses Cypher MERGE for upsert semantics.\n\nConfiguration\n\nPass a config dict with keys:\n\n\"url\" — Neo4j HTTP API URL (default \"http://localhost:7474\") Also accepts bolt/neo4j URLs (neo4j://host:port) — the host is extracted and HTTP port 7474 is used.\n\"username\" — required\n\"password\" — required\n\"database\" — database name (default \"neo4j\")\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.Neo4jGraphStore"},{"category":"function","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.generate_response","page":"Providers","text":"generate_response(llm, messages; response_format=nothing, tools=nothing, tool_choice=\"auto\")\n\nGenerate a response from the LLM. Must be implemented by all providers.\n\nArguments\n\nmessages: Vector of message dicts with \"role\" and \"content\" keys\nresponse_format: Optional format constraint (e.g., \"json\")\ntools: Optional vector of tool definitions for function calling\ntool_choice: Tool calling mode (\"auto\", \"required\", \"none\")\n\nReturns\n\nAn LLMResponse with content and optional tool_calls.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.generate_response"},{"category":"function","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.embed","page":"Providers","text":"embed(embedder, text; memory_action=nothing)\n\nGenerate an embedding vector for the given text.\n\nArguments\n\ntext: The text to embed\nmemory_action: Optional hint (\"add\", \"search\", \"update\") for action-aware embeddings\n\nReturns\n\nA Vector{Float64} embedding.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.embed"},{"category":"function","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.create_llm","page":"Providers","text":"create_llm(config::LlmConfig) → AbstractLLM\n\nInstantiate an LLM provider from configuration.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.create_llm"},{"category":"function","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.create_embedder","page":"Providers","text":"create_embedder(config::EmbedderConfig) → AbstractEmbedder\n\nInstantiate an embedding provider from configuration.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.create_embedder"},{"category":"function","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.create_vector_store","page":"Providers","text":"create_vector_store(config::VectorStoreConfig) → AbstractVectorStore\n\nInstantiate a vector store from configuration.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.create_vector_store"},{"category":"function","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.create_graph_store","page":"Providers","text":"create_graph_store(config::GraphStoreConfig, llm_config::LlmConfig, embedder_config::EmbedderConfig) → AbstractGraphStore\n\nInstantiate a graph store from configuration.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.create_graph_store"},{"category":"function","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.register_llm_provider!","page":"Providers","text":"register_llm_provider!(name, constructor)\n\nRegister a custom LLM provider.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.register_llm_provider!"},{"category":"function","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.register_embedder_provider!","page":"Providers","text":"register_embedder_provider!(name, constructor)\n\nRegister a custom embedding provider.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.register_embedder_provider!"},{"category":"function","location":"api/providers.html#Mem0.register_vector_store_provider!","page":"Providers","text":"register_vector_store_provider!(name, constructor)\n\nRegister a custom vector store provider.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.register_vector_store_provider!"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#getting_started","page":"Getting Started","text":"This guide walks you through installing Mem0.jl, understanding its core concepts, and building your first memory-powered application.","title":"Getting Started"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Installation","page":"Getting Started","text":"Mem0.jl is installed directly from its Git repository:\n\nusing Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/sdwfrost/Mem0.jl.git\")","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Prerequisites","page":"Getting Started","text":"Julia 1.9+\nAn LLM provider — either:\nOllama running locally (recommended for getting started)\nAn OpenAI API key\n\nIf using Ollama, pull the required models:\n\nollama pull qwen2.5\nollama pull nomic-embed-text","title":"Prerequisites"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Core-Concepts","page":"Getting Started","text":"Mem0.jl provides a self-improving memory layer for AI agents. Here's how the pieces fit together:","title":"Core Concepts"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Memory","page":"Getting Started","text":"The Memory type is the central orchestrator. It coordinates:\n\nLLM-based fact extraction — an LLM reads conversations and extracts discrete facts\nEmbedding generation — facts are converted to vector representations\nVector storage — embeddings are stored for fast similarity search\nDeduplication — the LLM decides whether new facts should be added, merged with existing memories, or ignored\nHistory tracking — every operation is logged in SQLite","title":"Memory"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Providers","page":"Getting Started","text":"Mem0.jl uses a provider abstraction for each component:\n\nComponent Abstract Type Available Providers\nLLM AbstractLLM OllamaLLM, OpenAILLM\nEmbeddings AbstractEmbedder OllamaEmbedding, OpenAIEmbedding\nVector Store AbstractVectorStore InMemoryVectorStore\nGraph Store AbstractGraphStore InMemoryGraphStore, Neo4jGraphStore","title":"Providers"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Configuration","page":"Getting Started","text":"All providers are configured through MemoryConfig, which holds sub-configs for each component. See Configuration for full details.","title":"Configuration"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Complete-Walkthrough","page":"Getting Started","text":"","title":"Complete Walkthrough"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Step-1:-Create-a-Memory-Instance","page":"Getting Started","text":"using Mem0\n\nconfig = MemoryConfig(\n    llm = LlmConfig(\n        provider = \"ollama\",\n        config = Dict(\"model\" => \"qwen2.5\", \"temperature\" => 0.1),\n    ),\n    embedder = EmbedderConfig(\n        provider = \"ollama\",\n        config = Dict(\"model\" => \"nomic-embed-text\", \"embedding_dims\" => 768),\n    ),\n    vector_store = VectorStoreConfig(\n        provider = \"in_memory\",\n        config = Dict(\"collection_name\" => \"my_memories\", \"embedding_model_dims\" => 768),\n    ),\n)\n\nmem = Memory(config=config)","title":"Step 1: Create a Memory Instance"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Step-2:-Add-Memories","page":"Getting Started","text":"Pass conversation text or message arrays to add. The LLM extracts facts automatically:\n\n# Add from a plain string\nadd(mem, \"My name is Alice and I work at Acme Corp as a data scientist.\"; user_id=\"alice\")\n\n# Add from a conversation (vector of message dicts)\nmessages = [\n    Dict(\"role\" => \"user\", \"content\" => \"I'm planning a trip to Japan next month.\"),\n    Dict(\"role\" => \"assistant\", \"content\" => \"That sounds exciting! Have you been before?\"),\n    Dict(\"role\" => \"user\", \"content\" => \"No, it's my first time. I love sushi and want to visit Kyoto.\"),\n]\nadd(mem, messages; user_id=\"alice\")\n\nThe LLM will extract facts like:\n\n\"Name is Alice\"\n\"Works at Acme Corp as a data scientist\"\n\"Planning a trip to Japan next month\"\n\"Loves sushi\"\n\"Wants to visit Kyoto\"","title":"Step 2: Add Memories"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Step-3:-Search-Memories","page":"Getting Started","text":"Use search to find relevant memories by semantic similarity:\n\nresults = search(mem, \"What does Alice do for work?\"; user_id=\"alice\")\n\nfor r in results[\"results\"]\n    println(\"Memory: \", r[\"memory\"])\n    println(\"Score:  \", round(r[\"score\"]; digits=3))\n    println()\nend","title":"Step 3: Search Memories"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Step-4:-Retrieve-All-Memories","page":"Getting Started","text":"Use get_all to list every memory for a user:\n\nall = get_all(mem; user_id=\"alice\")\nfor r in all[\"results\"]\n    println(\"- \", r[\"memory\"])\nend","title":"Step 4: Retrieve All Memories"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Step-5:-Update-and-Delete","page":"Getting Started","text":"You can update or delete individual memories by ID:\n\n# Get a specific memory by ID\nmemory_id = results[\"results\"][1][\"id\"]\nmem_data = get_memory(mem, memory_id)\nprintln(\"Current: \", mem_data[\"memory\"])\n\n# Update it\nupdate(mem, memory_id, \"Works at Acme Corp as a senior data scientist\")\n\n# Delete it\ndelete(mem, memory_id)","title":"Step 5: Update and Delete"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Step-6:-View-History","page":"Getting Started","text":"Every operation is tracked. Use history to see the audit trail:\n\nh = history(mem, memory_id)\nfor entry in h\n    println(entry[\"event\"], \": \", something(entry[\"new_memory\"], \"(deleted)\"))\nend","title":"Step 6: View History"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Step-7:-Reset","page":"Getting Started","text":"To clear all memories and history:\n\nreset!(mem)","title":"Step 7: Reset"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Skipping-LLM-Inference","page":"Getting Started","text":"If you want to store messages directly without LLM-based fact extraction, pass infer=false:\n\nadd(mem, \"Raw message to store verbatim\"; user_id=\"alice\", infer=false)","title":"Skipping LLM Inference"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/getting_started.html#Next-Steps","page":"Getting Started","text":"Configuration — customize providers, models, and prompts\nProviders — learn about each provider and how to create custom ones\nGraph Memory — enable entity-relationship extraction\nAPI Reference — full function signatures and docstrings","title":"Next Steps"},{"category":"section","location":"api/memory.html#memory_api","page":"Memory","text":"The Memory type is the main entry point for Mem0.jl. It orchestrates LLM-based fact extraction, embedding, vector search, optional graph memory, and history tracking.","title":"Memory API"},{"category":"section","location":"api/memory.html#Memory-Type","page":"Memory","text":"","title":"Memory Type"},{"category":"section","location":"api/memory.html#Adding-Memories","page":"Memory","text":"","title":"Adding Memories"},{"category":"section","location":"api/memory.html#Searching-Memories","page":"Memory","text":"","title":"Searching Memories"},{"category":"section","location":"api/memory.html#Updating-Memories","page":"Memory","text":"","title":"Updating Memories"},{"category":"section","location":"api/memory.html#Deleting-Memories","page":"Memory","text":"","title":"Deleting Memories"},{"category":"section","location":"api/memory.html#Retrieving-Memories","page":"Memory","text":"","title":"Retrieving Memories"},{"category":"section","location":"api/memory.html#History","page":"Memory","text":"","title":"History"},{"category":"section","location":"api/memory.html#Resetting","page":"Memory","text":"","title":"Resetting"},{"category":"type","location":"api/memory.html#Mem0.Memory","page":"Memory","text":"Memory\n\nThe main Mem0 memory system. Orchestrates LLM-based fact extraction, embedding, vector search, optional graph memory, and history tracking.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.Memory"},{"category":"function","location":"api/memory.html#Mem0.add","page":"Memory","text":"add(mem, messages; user_id=nothing, agent_id=nothing, run_id=nothing,\n    metadata=nothing, infer=true, memory_type=nothing, prompt=nothing)\n\nCreate new memories from messages. When infer=true (default), the LLM extracts facts from the conversation, deduplicates against existing memories, and decides whether to ADD, UPDATE, or DELETE. When infer=false, messages are stored directly.\n\nReturns a Dict with \"results\" and optionally \"relations\" keys.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.add"},{"category":"function","location":"api/memory.html#Mem0.search","page":"Memory","text":"search(mem, query; user_id=nothing, agent_id=nothing, run_id=nothing,\n       limit=100, filters=nothing, threshold=nothing)\n\nSearch memories by semantic similarity.\n\nReturns a Dict with \"results\" and optionally \"relations\" keys.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.search"},{"category":"function","location":"api/memory.html#Mem0.update","page":"Memory","text":"update(mem, memory_id, data; metadata=nothing)\n\nUpdate an existing memory's content and optionally its metadata.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.update"},{"category":"function","location":"api/memory.html#Mem0.delete","page":"Memory","text":"delete(mem, memory_id)\n\nDelete a memory by ID.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.delete"},{"category":"function","location":"api/memory.html#Mem0.get_memory","page":"Memory","text":"get_memory(mem, memory_id)\n\nRetrieve a single memory by ID.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.get_memory"},{"category":"function","location":"api/memory.html#Mem0.get_all","page":"Memory","text":"get_all(mem; user_id=nothing, agent_id=nothing, run_id=nothing,\n        filters=nothing, limit=100)\n\nGet all memories for given session IDs.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.get_all"},{"category":"function","location":"api/memory.html#Mem0.history","page":"Memory","text":"history(mem, memory_id)\n\nGet the change history for a specific memory.\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.history"},{"category":"function","location":"api/memory.html#Mem0.reset!","page":"Memory","text":"reset!(mem)\n\nReset all memories (vector store + graph + history).\n\n\n\n\n\n","title":"Mem0.reset!"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#providers_guide","page":"Providers","text":"Mem0.jl uses a provider abstraction to decouple the memory system from specific backend implementations. Each component — LLM, embedder, vector store, and graph store — has an abstract base type and one or more concrete providers.","title":"Providers"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#LLM-Providers","page":"Providers","text":"LLM providers generate text responses for fact extraction, memory update decisions, and entity/relationship extraction. All providers implement the generate_response method.","title":"LLM Providers"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#OllamaLLM","page":"Providers","text":"OllamaLLM connects to a locally running Ollama server. No API key required — ideal for local development and privacy-sensitive deployments.\n\nconfig = LlmConfig(\n    provider = \"ollama\",\n    config = Dict(\n        \"model\" => \"qwen2.5\",           # any Ollama model\n        \"base_url\" => \"http://localhost:11434\",\n        \"temperature\" => 0.1,\n        \"max_tokens\" => 2000,\n        \"top_p\" => 1.0,\n    ),\n)\n\nDefault model: llama3.1. The base_url defaults to ENV[\"OLLAMA_HOST\"] or http://localhost:11434.\n\ntip: Tip\nFor best results with fact extraction, use a model with strong JSON output support such as qwen2.5, llama3.1, or mistral.","title":"OllamaLLM"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#OpenAILLM","page":"Providers","text":"OpenAILLM uses the OpenAI Chat Completions API. Compatible with any OpenAI-compatible endpoint (Azure OpenAI, vLLM, LiteLLM, etc.) by setting a custom base_url.\n\nconfig = LlmConfig(\n    provider = \"openai\",\n    config = Dict(\n        \"model\" => \"gpt-4.1-nano-2025-04-14\",\n        \"api_key\" => ENV[\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"],\n        \"base_url\" => \"https://api.openai.com/v1\",\n        \"temperature\" => 0.1,\n        \"max_tokens\" => 2000,\n        \"top_p\" => 1.0,\n    ),\n)\n\nDefault model: gpt-4.1-nano-2025-04-14. The api_key defaults to ENV[\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"].","title":"OpenAILLM"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#Embedding-Providers","page":"Providers","text":"Embedding providers convert text into dense vector representations for similarity search. All providers implement the embed method.","title":"Embedding Providers"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#OllamaEmbedding","page":"Providers","text":"OllamaEmbedding uses Ollama's embedding API with local models:\n\nconfig = EmbedderConfig(\n    provider = \"ollama\",\n    config = Dict(\n        \"model\" => \"nomic-embed-text\",   # 768-dimensional embeddings\n        \"base_url\" => \"http://localhost:11434\",\n        \"embedding_dims\" => 768,\n    ),\n)\n\nDefault model: nomic-embed-text (768 dimensions).","title":"OllamaEmbedding"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#OpenAIEmbedding","page":"Providers","text":"OpenAIEmbedding uses the OpenAI Embeddings API:\n\nconfig = EmbedderConfig(\n    provider = \"openai\",\n    config = Dict(\n        \"model\" => \"text-embedding-3-small\",\n        \"api_key\" => ENV[\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"],\n        \"embedding_dims\" => 1536,\n    ),\n)\n\nDefault model: text-embedding-3-small (1536 dimensions). The dimensions parameter is automatically sent for text-embedding-3-* models.","title":"OpenAIEmbedding"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#Vector-Store-Providers","page":"Providers","text":"Vector stores hold embeddings and support similarity search with metadata filtering. They implement insert!, search, get, delete!, update!, list_records, and reset!.","title":"Vector Store Providers"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#InMemoryVectorStore","page":"Providers","text":"InMemoryVectorStore is a simple in-memory store using brute-force cosine similarity. Suitable for development, testing, and small-scale deployments.\n\nconfig = VectorStoreConfig(\n    provider = \"in_memory\",\n    config = Dict(\n        \"collection_name\" => \"my_memories\",\n        \"embedding_model_dims\" => 768,\n    ),\n)\n\nwarning: Warning\nData in InMemoryVectorStore is lost when the Julia process exits. For persistence, consider implementing a custom vector store provider backed by a database.","title":"InMemoryVectorStore"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#Graph-Store-Providers","page":"Providers","text":"Graph stores maintain entity-relationship networks extracted from conversations. They implement add_to_graph!, search_graph, delete_from_graph!, delete_all_graph!, and get_all_graph.","title":"Graph Store Providers"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#InMemoryGraphStore","page":"Providers","text":"InMemoryGraphStore stores nodes and edges in dictionaries with adjacency-list semantics. Supports entity embeddings for semantic matching, soft deletion, and multi-tenant filtering.\n\nconfig = MemoryConfig(\n    # ... llm and embedder config ...\n    graph_store = GraphStoreConfig(\n        provider = \"in_memory\",\n        config = Dict{String, Any}(),   # non-nothing enables graph\n        threshold = 0.7,\n    ),\n)","title":"InMemoryGraphStore"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#Neo4jGraphStore","page":"Providers","text":"Neo4jGraphStore persists the knowledge graph in a Neo4j database via the HTTP Transactional Cypher API. Uses MERGE for upsert semantics and stores entity embeddings as node properties.\n\nconfig = MemoryConfig(\n    # ... llm and embedder config ...\n    graph_store = GraphStoreConfig(\n        provider = \"neo4j\",\n        config = Dict{String, Any}(\n            \"url\" => \"http://localhost:7474\",\n            \"username\" => \"neo4j\",\n            \"password\" => \"your-password\",\n            \"database\" => \"neo4j\",\n        ),\n        threshold = 0.7,\n    ),\n)\n\nThe url field accepts http://, https://, bolt://, and neo4j:// URLs. For bolt/neo4j URLs, the host is extracted and HTTP port 7474 is used.\n\nSee Graph Memory for a detailed guide.","title":"Neo4jGraphStore"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#Factory-Functions","page":"Providers","text":"Providers are instantiated through factory functions that read the config and return the appropriate concrete type:\n\ncreate_llm — creates an AbstractLLM from LlmConfig\ncreate_embedder — creates an AbstractEmbedder from EmbedderConfig\ncreate_vector_store — creates an AbstractVectorStore from VectorStoreConfig\ncreate_graph_store — creates an AbstractGraphStore from GraphStoreConfig\n\nYou typically don't call these directly — the Memory constructor calls them for you. They're useful when building custom pipelines.","title":"Factory Functions"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#Implementing-Custom-Providers","page":"Providers","text":"","title":"Implementing Custom Providers"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#Custom-LLM","page":"Providers","text":"To create a custom LLM provider:\n\nDefine a struct that subtypes AbstractLLM\nImplement a Dict{String, Any} constructor for the factory pattern\nImplement generate_response\nRegister with register_llm_provider!\n\nusing Mem0\n\nstruct MyLLM <: AbstractLLM\n    model::String\n    endpoint::String\nend\n\nfunction MyLLM(config::Dict{String, Any})\n    MyLLM(\n        get(config, \"model\", \"default-model\"),\n        get(config, \"endpoint\", \"http://localhost:8080\"),\n    )\nend\n\nfunction Mem0.generate_response(llm::MyLLM, messages::Vector;\n                                response_format=nothing, tools=nothing,\n                                tool_choice=\"auto\")\n    # Call your LLM API here...\n    # Must return an LLMResponse\n    return LLMResponse(content=\"response text\", tool_calls=Dict{String, Any}[])\nend\n\nregister_llm_provider!(\"my_llm\", MyLLM)","title":"Custom LLM"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#Custom-Embedder","page":"Providers","text":"Subtype AbstractEmbedder\nImplement embed\nRegister with register_embedder_provider!\n\nstruct MyEmbedder <: AbstractEmbedder\n    model::String\n    dims::Int\nend\n\nMyEmbedder(config::Dict{String, Any}) = MyEmbedder(\n    get(config, \"model\", \"default\"),\n    get(config, \"embedding_dims\", 384),\n)\n\nfunction Mem0.embed(emb::MyEmbedder, text::AbstractString; memory_action=nothing)::Vector{Float64}\n    # Generate embedding vector here...\n    return zeros(Float64, emb.dims)  # placeholder\nend\n\nregister_embedder_provider!(\"my_embedder\", MyEmbedder)","title":"Custom Embedder"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/providers.html#Custom-Vector-Store","page":"Providers","text":"Subtype AbstractVectorStore\nImplement the required interface methods:\nBase.insert!(store, vectors, payloads, ids)\nMem0.search(store, query_vector, limit; filters, threshold)\nBase.delete!(store, vector_id)\nMem0.update!(store, vector_id; vector, payload)\nBase.get(store, vector_id)\nMem0.list_records(store; filters, limit)\nMem0.reset!(store)\nRegister with register_vector_store_provider!\n\nstruct MyVectorStore <: AbstractVectorStore\n    # your fields...\nend\n\nMyVectorStore(config::Dict{String, Any}) = MyVectorStore(...)\n\n# Implement all required methods...\n\nregister_vector_store_provider!(\"my_store\", MyVectorStore)","title":"Custom Vector Store"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Mem0.jl","page":"Home","text":"A self-improving memory layer for AI agents in Julia.\n\nMem0.jl is a Julia port of mem0 — providing LLM-based fact extraction, semantic vector search, optional graph memory, and full change history tracking. It enables AI agents and applications to remember user preferences, past interactions, and contextual knowledge across sessions.","title":"Mem0.jl"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Features","page":"Home","text":"LLM-powered fact extraction — automatically distills conversations into discrete, searchable facts\nSemantic vector search — find relevant memories using cosine similarity over embeddings\nGraph memory — optional entity-relationship extraction for structured knowledge (in-memory or Neo4j)\nHistory tracking — SQLite-backed audit trail of every add, update, and delete operation\nIntelligent deduplication — LLM-driven decisions to add, update, or delete memories based on new information\nMulti-tenant — filter memories by user_id, agent_id, or run_id\nMultiple providers — supports OpenAI and Ollama for both LLM and embedding backends\nExtensible factory pattern — register custom LLM, embedding, and vector store providers","title":"Features"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Installation","page":"Home","text":"using Pkg\nPkg.add(url=\"https://github.com/sdwfrost/Mem0.jl.git\")","title":"Installation"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Quick-Start","page":"Home","text":"using Mem0\n\n# Configure with Ollama (local, no API key needed)\nconfig = MemoryConfig(\n    llm = LlmConfig(provider=\"ollama\", config=Dict(\"model\" => \"qwen2.5\")),\n    embedder = EmbedderConfig(provider=\"ollama\", config=Dict(\"model\" => \"nomic-embed-text\", \"embedding_dims\" => 768)),\n    vector_store = VectorStoreConfig(provider=\"in_memory\", config=Dict(\"collection_name\" => \"demo\", \"embedding_model_dims\" => 768)),\n)\nmem = Memory(config=config)\n\n# Add memories from conversations\nadd(mem, \"I love programming in Julia and Python\"; user_id=\"alice\")\nadd(mem, \"My favorite editor is VS Code\"; user_id=\"alice\")\n\n# Search memories by semantic similarity\nresults = search(mem, \"What programming languages does she like?\"; user_id=\"alice\")\nfor r in results[\"results\"]\n    println(r[\"memory\"], \" (score: \", round(r[\"score\"]; digits=3), \")\")\nend\n\n# Retrieve all memories for a user\nall_memories = get_all(mem; user_id=\"alice\")","title":"Quick Start"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#Documentation-Overview","page":"Home","text":"","title":"Documentation Overview"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#[Guide](@ref-getting_started)","page":"Home","text":"Getting Started — installation, basic concepts, and a complete walkthrough\nConfiguration — all configuration options explained\nProviders — LLM, embedding, vector store, and graph store providers\nGraph Memory — entity-relationship extraction and graph-based search","title":"Guide"},{"category":"section","location":"index.html#[API-Reference](@ref-memory_api)","page":"Home","text":"Memory — the main Memory type and its public methods\nTypes — configuration structs, data types, and enums\nProviders — abstract interfaces and concrete provider implementations\nUtilities — helper functions for parsing, hashing, filtering, and more","title":"API Reference"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#configuration","page":"Configuration","text":"Mem0.jl is configured through a hierarchy of config structs. The top-level MemoryConfig holds sub-configurations for each component.","title":"Configuration"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#MemoryConfig","page":"Configuration","text":"MemoryConfig is the single entry point for all configuration:\n\nBase.@kwdef mutable struct MemoryConfig\n    llm::LlmConfig = LlmConfig()\n    embedder::EmbedderConfig = EmbedderConfig()\n    vector_store::VectorStoreConfig = VectorStoreConfig()\n    graph_store::GraphStoreConfig = GraphStoreConfig()\n    reranker::Union{Nothing, RerankerConfig} = nothing\n    history_db_path::String = \":memory:\"\n    version::String = \"v1.1\"\n    custom_fact_extraction_prompt::Union{Nothing, String} = nothing\n    custom_update_memory_prompt::Union{Nothing, String} = nothing\nend\n\nField Type Default Description\nllm LlmConfig OpenAI gpt-4.1-nano LLM provider for fact extraction and memory decisions\nembedder EmbedderConfig OpenAI text-embedding-3-small Embedding provider for vectorizing memories\nvector_store VectorStoreConfig In-memory store Backend for vector storage and similarity search\ngraph_store GraphStoreConfig In-memory (disabled) Optional graph memory for entity-relationship storage\nreranker RerankerConfig or nothing nothing Optional reranker configuration\nhistory_db_path String \":memory:\" SQLite database path for history (\":memory:\" for in-memory)\nversion String \"v1.1\" Configuration version string\ncustom_fact_extraction_prompt String or nothing nothing Override the default fact extraction system prompt\ncustom_update_memory_prompt String or nothing nothing Override the default memory update decision prompt","title":"MemoryConfig"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#LlmConfig","page":"Configuration","text":"Configures the language model used for fact extraction and memory management decisions:\n\nBase.@kwdef mutable struct LlmConfig\n    provider::String = \"openai\"\n    config::Dict{String, Any} = Dict{String, Any}(\n        \"model\" => \"gpt-4.1-nano-2025-04-14\",\n        \"temperature\" => 0.1,\n        \"max_tokens\" => 2000,\n    )\nend","title":"LlmConfig"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#Provider-specific-config-keys","page":"Configuration","text":"OpenAI (provider = \"openai\"):\n\nKey Type Default Description\n\"model\" String \"gpt-4.1-nano-2025-04-14\" Model name\n\"api_key\" String ENV[\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"] API key\n\"base_url\" String \"https://api.openai.com/v1\" API base URL\n\"temperature\" Float64 0.1 Sampling temperature\n\"max_tokens\" Int 2000 Maximum tokens in response\n\"top_p\" Float64 1.0 Nucleus sampling parameter\n\nOllama (provider = \"ollama\"):\n\nKey Type Default Description\n\"model\" String \"llama3.1\" Model name\n\"base_url\" String ENV[\"OLLAMA_HOST\"] or \"http://localhost:11434\" Ollama API URL\n\"temperature\" Float64 0.1 Sampling temperature\n\"max_tokens\" Int 2000 Maximum tokens (num_predict in Ollama)\n\"top_p\" Float64 1.0 Nucleus sampling parameter","title":"Provider-specific config keys"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#EmbedderConfig","page":"Configuration","text":"Configures the embedding model used for vectorizing memories and queries:\n\nBase.@kwdef mutable struct EmbedderConfig\n    provider::String = \"openai\"\n    config::Dict{String, Any} = Dict{String, Any}(\n        \"model\" => \"text-embedding-3-small\",\n        \"embedding_dims\" => 1536,\n    )\nend","title":"EmbedderConfig"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#Provider-specific-config-keys-2","page":"Configuration","text":"OpenAI (provider = \"openai\"):\n\nKey Type Default Description\n\"model\" String \"text-embedding-3-small\" Embedding model name\n\"api_key\" String ENV[\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"] API key\n\"base_url\" String \"https://api.openai.com/v1\" API base URL\n\"embedding_dims\" Int 1536 Output embedding dimensions\n\nOllama (provider = \"ollama\"):\n\nKey Type Default Description\n\"model\" String \"nomic-embed-text\" Embedding model name\n\"base_url\" String ENV[\"OLLAMA_HOST\"] or \"http://localhost:11434\" Ollama API URL\n\"embedding_dims\" Int 768 Output embedding dimensions\n\nwarning: Matching dimensions\nThe embedding_dims in EmbedderConfig must match the embedding_model_dims in VectorStoreConfig. A mismatch will cause incorrect similarity scores.","title":"Provider-specific config keys"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#VectorStoreConfig","page":"Configuration","text":"Configures the vector storage backend:\n\nBase.@kwdef mutable struct VectorStoreConfig\n    provider::String = \"in_memory\"\n    config::Dict{String, Any} = Dict{String, Any}(\n        \"collection_name\" => \"mem0\",\n        \"embedding_model_dims\" => 1536,\n    )\nend\n\nIn-memory (provider = \"in_memory\"):\n\nKey Type Default Description\n\"collection_name\" String \"mem0\" Name for the collection\n\"embedding_model_dims\" Int 1536 Expected embedding dimensions","title":"VectorStoreConfig"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#GraphStoreConfig","page":"Configuration","text":"Configures the optional graph memory backend. Graph memory is disabled by default — set config to a non-nothing dict to enable it:\n\nBase.@kwdef mutable struct GraphStoreConfig\n    provider::String = \"in_memory\"\n    config::Union{Nothing, Dict{String, Any}} = nothing\n    llm::Union{Nothing, LlmConfig} = nothing\n    custom_prompt::Union{Nothing, String} = nothing\n    threshold::Float64 = 0.7\nend\n\nField Type Default Description\nprovider String \"in_memory\" Graph backend: \"in_memory\" or \"neo4j\"\nconfig Dict or nothing nothing Provider config; nothing disables graph memory\nllm LlmConfig or nothing nothing Override LLM for graph extraction (falls back to main LLM)\ncustom_prompt String or nothing nothing Custom prompt for relationship extraction\nthreshold Float64 0.7 Cosine similarity threshold for entity matching\n\nSee Graph Memory for detailed setup.","title":"GraphStoreConfig"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#RerankerConfig","page":"Configuration","text":"Configuration for an optional result reranker:\n\nBase.@kwdef mutable struct RerankerConfig\n    provider::String = \"llm\"\n    config::Union{Nothing, Dict{String, Any}} = nothing\nend","title":"RerankerConfig"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#Configuration-Examples","page":"Configuration","text":"","title":"Configuration Examples"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#Minimal-Ollama-Setup","page":"Configuration","text":"config = MemoryConfig(\n    llm = LlmConfig(provider=\"ollama\", config=Dict(\"model\" => \"qwen2.5\")),\n    embedder = EmbedderConfig(provider=\"ollama\", config=Dict(\"model\" => \"nomic-embed-text\", \"embedding_dims\" => 768)),\n    vector_store = VectorStoreConfig(provider=\"in_memory\", config=Dict(\"collection_name\" => \"test\", \"embedding_model_dims\" => 768)),\n)","title":"Minimal Ollama Setup"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#OpenAI-with-Persistent-History","page":"Configuration","text":"config = MemoryConfig(\n    llm = LlmConfig(provider=\"openai\", config=Dict(\n        \"model\" => \"gpt-4.1-nano-2025-04-14\",\n        \"api_key\" => ENV[\"OPENAI_API_KEY\"],\n    )),\n    embedder = EmbedderConfig(provider=\"openai\", config=Dict(\n        \"model\" => \"text-embedding-3-small\",\n        \"embedding_dims\" => 1536,\n    )),\n    vector_store = VectorStoreConfig(provider=\"in_memory\", config=Dict(\n        \"collection_name\" => \"production\",\n        \"embedding_model_dims\" => 1536,\n    )),\n    history_db_path = \"memory_history.sqlite\",\n)","title":"OpenAI with Persistent History"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#With-Graph-Memory-Enabled","page":"Configuration","text":"config = MemoryConfig(\n    llm = LlmConfig(provider=\"ollama\", config=Dict(\"model\" => \"qwen2.5\")),\n    embedder = EmbedderConfig(provider=\"ollama\", config=Dict(\"model\" => \"nomic-embed-text\", \"embedding_dims\" => 768)),\n    vector_store = VectorStoreConfig(provider=\"in_memory\", config=Dict(\"collection_name\" => \"test\", \"embedding_model_dims\" => 768)),\n    graph_store = GraphStoreConfig(\n        provider = \"in_memory\",\n        config = Dict{String, Any}(),  # non-nothing enables graph memory\n        threshold = 0.7,\n    ),\n)","title":"With Graph Memory Enabled"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#Custom-Fact-Extraction-Prompt","page":"Configuration","text":"config = MemoryConfig(\n    llm = LlmConfig(provider=\"ollama\", config=Dict(\"model\" => \"qwen2.5\")),\n    embedder = EmbedderConfig(provider=\"ollama\", config=Dict(\"model\" => \"nomic-embed-text\", \"embedding_dims\" => 768)),\n    vector_store = VectorStoreConfig(provider=\"in_memory\", config=Dict(\"collection_name\" => \"test\", \"embedding_model_dims\" => 768)),\n    custom_fact_extraction_prompt = \"\"\"\n    You are a medical information organizer. Extract only medically relevant facts\n    from conversations: symptoms, diagnoses, medications, allergies, and vital signs.\n    Return as JSON: {\"facts\": [\"fact1\", \"fact2\", ...]}\n    \"\"\",\n)","title":"Custom Fact Extraction Prompt"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#Environment-Variables","page":"Configuration","text":"Mem0.jl reads the following environment variables as defaults:\n\nVariable Used by Description\nOPENAI_API_KEY OpenAILLM, OpenAIEmbedding OpenAI API authentication key\nOPENAI_API_BASE OpenAILLM, OpenAIEmbedding Custom OpenAI-compatible API base URL\nOLLAMA_HOST OllamaLLM, OllamaEmbedding Ollama server URL (default: http://localhost:11434)","title":"Environment Variables"},{"category":"section","location":"guide/configuration.html#Custom-Provider-Registration","page":"Configuration","text":"You can register custom providers at runtime using the factory registration functions:\n\nusing Mem0\n\n# Define a custom LLM type\nstruct MyCustomLLM <: AbstractLLM\n    model::String\nend\nMyCustomLLM(config::Dict{String, Any}) = MyCustomLLM(get(config, \"model\", \"default\"))\n\n# Implement the required interface\nfunction Mem0.generate_response(llm::MyCustomLLM, messages::Vector; kwargs...)\n    # ... your implementation ...\nend\n\n# Register it\nregister_llm_provider!(\"my_custom\", MyCustomLLM)\n\n# Now use it in config\nconfig = MemoryConfig(\n    llm = LlmConfig(provider=\"my_custom\", config=Dict(\"model\" => \"my-model\")),\n    # ...\n)\n\nSee Providers for full details on implementing custom providers.","title":"Custom Provider Registration"}]
}
